The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gill to meet Fifa chief
                                                   Gill to meet Fifa chief
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The union sports minister, M. S. Gill, who was criticised by national coach Bob Houghton for his anti-football comments recently, seems determined to prove his detractors wrong.         
	On Tuesday, the sports minister will leave for Zurich to meet Fifa president Sepp Blatter and hold a detailed discussion on his plans to improve the standard of Indian football.         
	This is the first time that an Indian sports minister will officially visit the Fifa headquarters and meet the head of the world soccer body.         
	Gill will be accompanied by the All India Football Federation (AIFF) secretary, Alberto Colaco.         
	According to sources, so keen was Gill to meet Blatter that Fifa extended an invitation to him to meet the president sometime between Tuesday and Friday.         
	The minister is expected urge the Fifa president to allot India at least one big tournament that will help the country to improve its infrastructure and other facilities.                                                                                                                       
